1) Install the latest version of django from svn
2) Edit settings.py, and change to customize: database, ...
3) Install the settings and create the initial DB:
		# python manage.py syncdb
4) Run the django server (don't use on production, only for dev or testing):
		# python manage.py runserver
5) Check all it's OK ...
6) Configure the webserver .. may be apache, ex:

	<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerName panel.sambadarua.org
    ServerAdmin webmaster@sambadarua.org

    DocumentRoot /var/www/sdrpanel/
    <Directory /var/www/>
        Options Indexes FollowSymLinks MultiViews
        AllowOverride All
        Order allow,deny
        Allow from All
        Deny from none
    </Directory>

    ErrorLog /var/log/apache2/sdrpanel-error.log

    LogLevel warn
    CustomLog /var/log/apache2/sdrpanel-access.log combined


    Alias /favicon.ico /var/www/sdrpanel/favicon.ico

    <Location "/">
        SetHandler python-program
        PythonHandler django.core.handlers.modpython
        SetEnv DJANGO_SETTINGS_MODULE sdrpanel.settings
        PythonDebug On
        PythonPath "['/var/www/'] + sys.path"
    </Location>

    <Location "/media">
        SetHandler None
    </Location>

    <LocationMatch "\.(jpg|gif|png)$">
        SetHandler None
    </LocationMatch>
	</VirtualHost>

